description: Russian President Vladimir Putin has congratulated Donald Trump on his election victory, saying he is ready to engage with the incoming U.S. president, according to npr.org.
title: Putin congratulates Trump, says 'ready' to engage in dialogue

description: TEHRAN - Mohammad Javad Zarif, a senior foreign policy aide to President Pezeshkian, said on Thursday the result of the U.S.  elections showed that Americans had clearly rejected “a shameful year of US complicity in Israel’s genocide in Gaza and carnage in Lebanon”.
title: Iran's Zarif: Election showed Americans oppose complicity in Gaza genocide

description: European leaders have urged incoming US President-elect Donald Trump to support Ukraine against Russia and avoid trade wars with European peers.
title: European leaders call on Trump to support Ukraine, avoid trade wars

description: TEHRAN - Iran supports Armenia’s sovereignty and territorial integrity and welcomes Yerevan’s efforts aimed at establishing friendly relations with its neighbors, Iranian Ambassador to Armenia Mehdi Sobhani has said, Armenpress reports.
title: Ambassador says Iran welcomes Armenia’s Crossroads of Peace initiative

description: Germany’s government coalition has collapsed in dramatic fashion after Chancellor Olaf Scholz fired Finance Minister Christian Lindner of the pro-business Free Democrats in a late-night move following a marathon of crisis meetings.
title: Germany faces sudden turmoil after ruling coalition collapses

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Foreign Ministry has said Tehran will judge the new U.S. government on the basis of its policies and approaches after Donald Trump won the presidential election on November 5.
title: Tehran says will judge new US president based on his policies

description: The head of the UN agency for Palestinian refugees said on Wednesday that UNRWA is in its “darkest hour”, and urged the international community to prevent Israel from enacting a ban on its operations in areas under Israeli control.
title: UNRWA urges world to block implementation of Israel’s ban

description: TEHRAN - President Masoud Pezeshkian said on Thursday that it "does make a difference" for Iran who has won the presidential elections in the United States, noting Iran and its political system is reliant on its own power and its great and noble nation.
title: Pezeshkian: It makes no difference for Iran who has won the White House

description: TEHRAN - The AFC U20 Asian Cup China 2025 is primed for thrilling action following the conclusion of the official draw at Grand Skylight International Guanlan in Shenzhen, China on Thursday.
title: Iran learn fate at AFC U20 Asian Cup 2025

description: TEHRAN - Sokol Cikalleshi’s first half hat-trick powered Tractor to a 7-0 defeat of Tajikistan’s FC Ravshan on Wednesday as the side from Iran booked their place in the knockout rounds of the AFC Champions League Two 2024/25.
title: Tractor into 2024/25 AFC Champions League Two knockout stage
